configset listname maxlength = [VALUE]
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Default Value : 40000
Data Type     : integer
Category      : moderate
Password Notes: Visible only with password. 
= = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =

EXAMPLE:
configset listname maxlength = 100000


$INCLUDE-config/maxlength

Setting this value to zero will disable the body length check.

The length of the body of a message is stored in the "body_length"
access variable.  If the limit is exceeded, the "body_length_exceeded"
access variable will be set to 1.  See "help configset_access_rules" and
"help access_variables" for more information on access variables. 


See Also:
   help access_variables 
   help admin_moderate
   help configset_access_rules
   help configset_admin_body
   help configset_max_header_line_length
   help configset_max_mime_header_length
   help configset_max_total_header_length
   help configset_taboo_body

